author: ELIZABETH ELIZALDE
title: Plane carrying 5 people crashes into Australian shopping mall
text:
Plane carrying five people crashes into Australian shopping mall Plane carrying 5 people crashes into Australian shopping mall The plane carrying five people crashed near Essendon Airport in Melbourne, Australia Tuesday. (AP) NEW YORK DAILY NEWS  32 PM 
A small aircraft carrying five people crashed into a shopping mall near Essendon Airport in Melbourne, Australia, Tuesday, according to local reports. 
The pilot and four American passengers – believed to be golfers – were en route to King Island when the plane exploded before 9 a.m., according to a New Zealand TV station . Emergency personnel work at a light plane crashed in Melbourne, Australia, Tuesday. (Joe Castro/AP) 
The station reported that the pilot managed to send and emergency call, describing a “catastrophic engine failure” before the crash. The plane was en route to King Island when it crashed before 9 a.m., authorities said. (AP) 
"It appears to be a very, very tragic accident that's occurred out here," Victoria state police minister Lisa Neville told Sky News, adding that the impact could have caused fatalities. A fire crew at the scene where a light plane crashed into the back of a DFO building at Essendon airport in Melbourne, Australia. (JOE CASTRO/EPA) 
The crash happened about an hour before the Direct Factory Outlet shopping mall was supposed to open, police said. Police said the impact could have caused fatalities. (AP) 
So far, authorities have not confirmed any deaths. 
A taxi driver witnessed the crash and described it as a “massive fireball.” 
"I could feel the heat through the window of the taxi, and then a wheel - it looked like a plane wheel - bounced on the road and hit the front of the taxi as we were driving along,” the driver told Sky News . Join the Conversation:
